@djrm here are the changes for the theme.

I also added the line for the menu buttons top left.
(it was a bug that they were gone. but do you want to keep them?)

**Operating system or device, Godot version, GPU Model and driver (if graphics related):**
Arch linux; Godot 3.0 master branch

**Issue description:**
I am trying to remove rigid body when it collides with other.
It stops the process if I use node.free() or node.remove_and_skip() or node.get_parent().remove_child(node)
I understand, that I should use node.queue_free(), but process should not stops without any error. But it does.

When I tried to debug process, I found an issue:
in file space_2d_sw.cpp (I added comments on lines):

	void Space2DSW::call_queries() {
		while (state_query_list.first()) {

			Body2DSW *b = state_query_list.first()->self();
			b->call_queries(); // as I understand from this callback body will be freed
			state_query_list.remove(state_query_list.first()); // and here state_query_list.first() is null and it fails in remove() method
		}

		while (monitor_query_list.first()) {

			Area2DSW *a = monitor_query_list.first()->self();
			a->call_queries();
			monitor_query_list.remove(monitor_query_list.first());
		}
	}

I think, that it is better to store state_query_list.first() in variable to remove it correctly after b->call_queries()

And other problem, that process stops without any error. So it was pretty hard to find root of the problem. So maybe it should write an error to the output.

**Example project:**
[bug_example.zip](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/files/1272126/bug_example.zip)
